<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 9: LUBRICATING OIL PUMP, OIL FILTER AND
        COOLER - OIL FILTER AND HEADER
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>OIL FILTER AND HEADER</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
            <title>REMOVAL</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using a open end wrench, loosen and remove oil feed supply tube nut located on top of
                    oil filter header. Remove and discard tube nut O-Ring. Cap fitting on header (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600916">9.16</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With oil and coolant drained from the engine, remove the oil filter using an appropriate
                    filter wrench. Discard the filter (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600917">9.17</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1600916" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5026" filename="../figeg5/EG5026.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9.16 Removing Oil Supply Tube</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600917" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5035" filename="../figeg5/EG5035.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9.17 Removing Oil Filter</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Remove oil cooler and water coolant supply tube as an assembly.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove one (1) bolt and retainer plate securing water coolant supply tube from crankcase
                    (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600918">9.18</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove mounting hardware securing oil cooler assembly to crankcase (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600918">9.18</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1600918" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5037" filename="../figeg5/EG5037.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9.18 Removing Oil Cooler Mounting Bolts</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">1. Retainer Plate and Mounting Bolt</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">2. Oil Cooler</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">3. Oil Cooler Mounting Hardware</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove oil cooler and water coolant supply tube as an assembly from crankcase. Discard
                    O-Rings, gaskets and seals (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600919">9.19</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1600919" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5039" filename="../figeg5/EG5039.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9.19 Removing Oil Cooler</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
